XTGEOIP(1)

# NAME

xtgeoip - Build and manage xt_geoip data from MaxMind GeoLite2 CSVs.

# SYNOPSIS

*xtgeoip* [*-b*] [*-c*] [*-p*] [*-f*]++
*xtgeoip* _command_ [_options_]

# DESCRIPTION

*xtgeoip* downloads MaxMind GeoLite2 CSV databases and converts them into
binary IP range files for the Linux _xt\_geoip_ kernel module.

# COMMANDS

*build* [*-b*] [*-c*] [*-p*] [*-f*] [*-l*]
	Build xt_geoip database

*conf* *-d*|*-e*|*-s*
	Manage configuration

	*-d*
		Delete configuration

	*-e*
		Edit configuration

	*-s*
		Show configuration

*fetch* [*-p*]
	Fetch GeoLite2 data files

*run* [*-b*] [*-c*] [*-p*] [*-f*] [*-l*]
	Run full pipeline

# OPTIONS

*-b*, *--backup*
	Back up current database before replacing it.

*-c*, *--clean*
	Clean working files before continuing.

*-f*, *--force*
	Force the relevant operation when supported.

*-l*, *--legacy*
	Enable legacy mode.

*-p*, *--prune*
	Prune retained artifacts for the current operation.

# EXAMPLES

```
xtgeoip -h
xtgeoip -b
xtgeoip -c
xtgeoip -b -c
xtgeoip -b -p
xtgeoip build
xtgeoip build -l
xtgeoip build -b -p
xtgeoip build -c -f
xtgeoip build -b -c -p
xtgeoip conf -s
xtgeoip conf -d
xtgeoip conf -e
xtgeoip fetch
xtgeoip fetch -p
xtgeoip run
xtgeoip run -l
xtgeoip run -p
xtgeoip run -c -p
xtgeoip run -c -f
```

